.TH "__close_range" 9 "__close_range" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
__close_range \- Close all file descriptors in a given range.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" __close_range
.BI "(unsigned fd "  ","
.BI "unsigned max_fd "  ","
.BI "unsigned int flags "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "fd" 12
starting file descriptor to close
.IP "max_fd" 12
last file descriptor to close
.IP "flags" 12
-- undescribed --
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This closes a range of file descriptors. All file descriptors
from \fIfd\fP up to and including \fImax_fd\fP are closed.
